threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: Bourne-Again shell script, ASCII text executable

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This script initiates by clearing the terminal and displaying a message. It defines a list of specific file paths, primarily targeting configuration and credential files for various services (e.g., SSH, cloud providers, Docker, file transfer clients, cryptocurrency wallets). The script then iterates through this list, searching for the existence of these files within the `/root/` directory (if executed as root) and within the home directories of all users listed in `/home/`. If a specified file is found, its full path is printed to the console. Following the search, the script clears the shell command history and the terminal screen. No remote file downloads are initiated by this script.
